  <div class="container">
    <div class="biography-text">
      <p>The band has been together <strong>since 2013</strong> consisting of 3 members playing, 1 acoustic and 1 electric guitar and a kick-ass drum beat. At the end of 2013 they decided to evolve their own creativity by starting to write their own music and gigging all around Bloemfontein as they are <strong>a proud Bloem local based act</strong>.</p><p>As recent as June 2014 they released a studio recorded EP named <strong>‘ABIUA’</strong> and from there on promoted towards the project while finding themselves the number one alternative act in Bloemfontein on <strong>Reverbnation</strong>. ‘Die Mystic Boer’ has also announced Having Cows the number one ‘up and coming’ band for 2014 by <strong>winning the Crooked Boer Sessions</strong> in August 2014 and received a partial recording contract to share a compilation CD with fellow great Bloem bands.</p><p>Since November 2015 the band has evolved into the four piece line-up that they find themselves in currently, moving more towards the ‘plugged-in’ vibe doing full band shows. Classified as an <strong>indie band with a twitch of breaking the rules</strong> here and there, the guys from Having Cows play gigs all over South Africa. Proudly opening for local S.A. favourites like <strong>'aKING', ‘Monark’, ‘Moses&nbsp;Metro Man’, ‘Elvis Blue’ and ‘Shortstraw’</strong> in between gigging numerous shows in the city of roses as they stand well known for locally.</p><p>The band has enjoyed some radio play on Tuks FM with the single ‘A Beat In Us All’ off the ABIUA EP in early 2015 and entered the <strong>Tuks FM top 30</strong> charts while sticking around there for 12 weeks on-going peaking at <strong>number 11</strong>. Released on February 2016, they released ‘Tryna Be Lawful’ as a single track which has also been kindly received by <strong>Tuks FM, Kovsie FM and PUK FM</strong> and can be found on these radio stations’ rotational playlists.</p><p>Taking the bigger step towards recording at a more well-known production studio, they worked with <strong>Greg Carlin (Zebra & Giraffe)</strong> at OpenRoom Production studios with Greg producing their single ‘So Much To Gain’. The song was released in late April 2017 through MiniBeast Records as the official distributors.</p><p>Be sure to find the band on any social media platforms and gigging around wherever they are.</p>
